## CSS Variables Naming

`toCssKeyFormat()` converts camelCase keys to kebab-case: `primary600` → `primary-600`, `1.5x` → `1-5x`.

| Scope | Pattern | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Light mode colors | `--lm-color-{group}-{shade}` | `--lm-color-primary-600` |
| Dark mode colors | `--dm-color-{group}-{shade}` | `--dm-color-neutral-900` |
| Semantic colors | `--color-{group}-{shade}` | `--color-primary-600` |
| Light mode gradients | `--lm-gradient-primary-{shade}` | `--lm-gradient-primary-600` |
| Dark mode gradients | `--dm-gradient-primary-{shade}` | `--dm-gradient-primary-600` |
| Semantic gradients | `--gradient-primary-{shade}` | `--gradient-primary-600` |
| Sizes | `--size-{key}` | `--size-4x` |
| Spacing | `--spacing-{key}` | `--spacing-2x` |
| Rounding | `--rounding-{key}` | `--rounding-1-5x` |
| Border sizes | `--border-size-{key}` | `--border-size-thin` |
| Typography | `--typography-{style}` | `--typography-h1-medium` |

### Mode Switching

Semantic variables (`--color-*`, `--gradient-*`) are set under `[data-ui-mode="dark"]` / `[data-ui-mode="light"]` selectors and reference their mode-specific counterparts via `var(--dm-color-*)`.

```html
<html data-ui-mode="light"> ... </html>
```

